## 2) Project goal
Simulate temporal earthquake catalogs, group by the count of high-magnitude events (â‰¥ 5.0), visualize patterns, and fit Bayesian ETAS models with `ETAS.inlabru`.

## 3) Data/Simulation summary
- True parameters: Î¼ = 0.1, K = 0.089, Î± = 2.29, c = 0.11, p = 1.08
- Time window: T âˆˆ [0, 1000], multiple synthetic catalogs
- Grouping by # of high-magnitude events: 0, 1â€“2, 3â€“4, 5+

## 4) How to reproduce (when Rmd is available)
If you add the Rmd later, install dependencies and render:
```r
install.packages(c("rmarkdown","ETAS.inlabru","ggplot2","gridExtra","dplyr","future"))
rmarkdown::render("report/ETAS_simulation.Rmd", output_format = "pdf_document")
```

### knitr options to keep figures
In your Rmd setup chunk you can force figures to save into `figures/`:
```r
knitr::opts_chunk$set(fig.path = "figures/", dpi = 300, fig.width = 7, fig.height = 4.5)
```

## 5) How to use this repo now (PDF-only)
You can publish the PDF as primary artifact and add screenshots to the README:
```markdown
ðŸ“„ Full report (PDF): [code.pdf](./code.pdf)
```
*(Optional)* Export a few key figures from the PDF into `figures/` and embed:
```markdown
![Magnitude vs Time](./figures/mag_vs_time_sample1.png)
![Cumulative events](./figures/cum_events_sample1.png)
```

